# RetinaSafe — API Documentation
**Version:** 1.0 · **Base URL:** `http://localhost:8000` (dev) · `https://api.retinasafe.app` (prod)

All requests/responses use JSON unless noted. Timestamps are ISO 8601 UTC.

---

## Architecture & Data Flow

```
Step 1  Medical History        ──  client-side only (localStorage)
           │
Step 2  Image Upload           ──  POST /api/upload-image
           │ returns session_id
           │  ↳ CNN runs async in background
           │  ↳ frontend polls GET /api/model-result/:sessionId silently
           │
Step 3  Vision Games (×4)     ──  POST /api/game-result (after each game)
           │ also saved to localStorage as fallback
           │
Step 4  Report                 ──  POST /api/compute-report
           │ fuses model output + all 4 game results
           ↓
        GET /api/report/:reportId/pdf   (download)
        POST /api/save-to-dashboard     (persist to history, optional)
        GET  /api/health                (health check)
```

---

## Endpoint Reference

---

### 1. POST `/api/upload-image`

Upload a fundus photograph and begin model inference.

**Content-Type:** `multipart/form-data`

| Field | Type | Required | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `image` | File | ✅ | JPEG / PNG / TIFF, max 10 MB |
| `session_id` | string | ✅ | Client UUID from `RetinaSafeSession.get().sessionId` |
| `medical_history` | JSON string | ✗ | Stringified — see shape below |

```json
// medical_history shape
{
  "age_group": "45-59",
  "gender": "female",
  "last_exam": "1-2yr",
  "conditions": ["diabetes", "hypertension"]
}
```
`conditions` allowed values: `"diabetes"`, `"hypertension"`, `"smoking"`, `"family-history"`

**Response 200:**
```json
{
  "session_id": "srv-a1b2c3d4",
  "status": "queued",
  "message": "Image received. Model inference queued."
}
```
Store `session_id` — it is the backend's ID, which may differ from the client UUID.

**Errors:** `400` missing image · `415` wrong format · `413` too large · `500` queue unavailable

