## Integration Checklist

### Backend developer
- [ ] Implement all 7 endpoints with CORS (`Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *` in dev)
- [ ] `/api/upload-image` queues model inference, returns immediately with `"queued"`
- [ ] `/api/compute-report` handles `null` model_output (game-only fusion fallback)
- [ ] Store all game results + model output under `session_id` for audit trail
- [ ] Implement PDF generation (`/api/report/:id/pdf`) — WeasyPrint / Puppeteer recommended
- [ ] Set `window.RS_API_BASE = 'https://your-backend.com'` in a `<script>` before `api-bridge.js`

### Frontend developer — per game page
- [ ] Add before `</body>` of every game HTML:
  ```html
  <script src="session.js"></script>
  <script src="api-bridge.js"></script>
  <script src="game-collector.js"></script>
  ```
- [ ] In each game's end-game / showResults function, call:
  ```javascript
  RetinaSafeCollector.submit(finalPayload);
  ```
- [ ] `finalPayload.game_name` must exactly match one of the 4 canonical names above
- [ ] Comment out `RetinaSafeAPI.enableMock()` in `screening.js` when backend is live

### Notes on AI Analysis step removal
The previous "AI Analysis" wizard step has been **removed**. The model now runs silently while
the user plays games (~7–10 min). If inference isn't done by the time they click "Generate Report",
`computeReport` is still called and the backend applies game-only fusion. No spinner screen needed.